neric` and pre-fills a repeatable seeded target so users can manually rerun the protocol call\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:108:- Generic target select controls should show the current preset/auth-mode meaning inline, not only in hidden hover text, so users can understand how the request will change before running it\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:109:- The standalone inspector UI should provide a no-auth/Basic/Bearer authorization helper for generic MCP targets so users do not have to hand-build common Authorization headers\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:110:- The standalone inspector UI should provide Mock route presets for `/mcp/none`, `/mcp/basic`, and `/mcp/oauth`, using the visible Mock Server base URL and filling common auth fields only when the user selects a preset\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:111:- The standalone inspector UI should provide a Mock OAuth `client_credentials` token helper for the `/mcp/oauth` preset while still using the standard Mock Server `/oauth/token` endpoint\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:112:- The Generic MCP target page should include upstream Inspector-inspired helpers for copying the current server target JSON, importing a target JSON preset, and reviewing compact in-page request history\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:113:- The standalone inspector UI may remember non-secret local target settings in browser storage, but must not persist headers, Basic passwords, Bearer tokens, OAuth client secrets, root passwords, reset choices, or tool argument payloads\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:8:- MCP clients call `resources/*`, `prompts/*`, and `completion/complete` over existing Streamable HTTP and legacy SSE routes.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:15:- Completion supports prompt arguments and resource-template arguments through `completion/complete` with prefix matching, maximum 100 returned values, optional total, and `hasMore`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:26:- `resources/list` returns enabled direct resources, supports cursor pagination, and includes URI, name, title, description, MIME type, size, and annotations when present.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:27:- `resources/templates/list` returns enabled templates with URI template, name, title, description, MIME type, and annotations when present.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:28:- `resources/read` returns text or blob contents for a direct URI or a rendered template URI.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:29:- `resources/subscribe` and `resources/unsubscribe` are supported only for live legacy SSE sessions and return empty success results for valid accessible resources. Subscription state is process-local and best-effort; it is not stored in SQLite and is not replayed after disconnects, restarts, or cross-process handoff.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:30:- `prompts/list` returns enabled prompts, supports cursor pagination, and includes name, title, description, and argument metadata.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:31:- `prompts/get` validates required arguments and returns ordered prompt messages with substituted text and optional embedded resource content.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:32:- `completion/complete` supports `ref/prompt` by prompt name and `ref/resource` by URI template.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:42:| `/inspector` | Verification hub with project and upstream Inspector guidance |\ndocs/FEATURES.md:69:OAuth tokens also carry resource and prompt permission claims. Bearer `resources/list`, `resources/read`, `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and `completion/complete` expose only the permitted resource or prompt set.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:107:- direct Resources through `resources/list` and `resources/read`\ndocs/FEATURES.md:108:- Resource Templates through `resources/templates/list`, templated `resources/read`, and resource argument completion\ndocs/FEATURES.md:109:- Prompts through `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and prompt argument completion\ndocs/FEATURES.md:110:- `completion/complete` for prompt arguments and resource-template arguments\ndocs/FEATURES.md:111:- best-effort legacy SSE `resources/subscribe` / `resources/unsubscribe` with `notifications/resources/updated`, `notifications/resources/list_changed`, and `notifications/prompts/list_changed`\ndocs/FEATURES.md:119:- **Standalone project Inspector UI**: `npm run inspector:ui`, then open `http://127.0.0.1:3200` for Mock Server scenario, Generic method presets, and OAuth popup verification.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:120:- **Project CLI smoke Inspector**: `npm run inspector:mock`.\ndocs/FEATURES.md:121:- **Upstream MCP Inspector**: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector` for browser and CLI tools/resources/prompts checks. Upstream CLI `0.21.2` does not expose `completion/complete`; use the upstream browser UI or project Generic target for completion.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:11:5. `031-mcp-resources-runtime.md` -> `mcp-resources-runtime` -> Implement `resources/list`, `resources/templates/list`, and `resources/read` over existing MCP transports.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:12:6. `032-mcp-prompts-completion-runtime.md` -> `mcp-prompts-completion-runtime` -> Implement `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and `completion/complete`.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:15:9. `035-inspector-full-server-features.md` -> `inspector-full-server-features` -> Update Inspector/docs and prove full server-side MCP feature coverage end to end.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:34:- `025-inspector-compatibility-pack` and `026-inspector-popup-oauth-flow` are completed history and are intentionally not part of this active wave.\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:45:  console.log(`MCP Mock Server local inspector\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:48:  npm run inspector:mock\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:49:  npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3100\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:50:  ROOT_PASSWORD=change-this npm run inspector:mock -- --include-reset\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:265:    const posted = await mcp(client, endpoint, { j